Tegmina & hind wings. Male & female . Tegmina macropterous ( Figs 3a , 5a , 6b , 7a , 9a ) or submacropterous ( Figs 2a , 6a , 10a ). Hind wing usually reduced, ½ as wide and ¾ as long as tegmina, jugal lobe present, small. ( Figs 1i , 2f , 7h&i ,
9g
), M1+2 sometimes fused to R4+5. Rarely hind wing fully developed (256 specimen’s wings examined, 12 specimens with hind wing as long and wide as tegmina).

